  "text": "The minimal GCC GIMPLE optimization pass implementation counts basic blocks per function. The pass follows established GCC patterns found in the codebase: (1) The pass_data struct is defined following the pattern in gcc/tree-pass.h, specifying the pass metadata including type (GIMPLE_PASS), name, optimization flags (OPTGROUP_NONE), and property requirements. (2) The gimple_opt_pass class defined in gcc/tree-pass.h is inherited to create pass_block_counter, implementing the required virtual methods gate() and execute(). The gate() method returns true to enable the pass, while execute() performs the core logic. (3) The factory function make_pass_block_counter() is created following the pattern established by functions like make_pass_dce() in gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc. (4) The pass iterates over basic blocks using the FOR_EACH_BB_FN macro from gcc/basic-block.h, which provides standard iteration over control flow graph blocks. (5) Debug output is written using dump_file (standard GCC pattern), following examples from gcc/gimple-crc-optimization.cc and gcc/gimple-array-bounds.cc. The implementation demonstrates the complete structure needed for a GIMPLE pass: defining pass_data with properties_required set to PROP_cfg, implementing both gate() and execute() virtual methods, creating a factory function, and using dump_file for debug output when available."
}

